    {
      "id": "RQ-0001",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Reject agent-browser JSON envelopes that omit success",
      "description": "Principles violated: E) Make bugs hard to write, F) Fail fast, J) Consistency/Integrity.\n\nWhy it matters: the parser currently accepts any JSON object as an upstream envelope and the executor only treats `success === false` as failure. A malformed `agent-browser --json` response like `{ \"error\": \"boom\" }` therefore becomes a successful empty tool result with summary `open completed`, which hides upstream protocol failures from the agent and can poison later session state.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: tighten envelope validation so non-batch JSON objects must include a boolean `success`, or otherwise fail closed when an `error` field is present without an explicit success value. Add one parser-level regression and one end-to-end fake-binary regression through `agentBrowserExtension`.\n\nAcceptance criteria: `npm test` stays green; a fake `agent-browser` binary that emits `{ \"error\": \"boom\" }` at exit code 0 returns `isError: true`, surfaces a useful error string, and no longer summarizes the call as `open completed`.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "correctness",
        "protocol"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/envelope.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.test.ts",
        "npx tsx"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/envelope.ts:70-78 :: parseAgentBrowserEnvelope accepts any JSON object as an envelope, even when `success` is missing.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/envelope.ts:94-108 :: getAgentBrowserErrorText only reports envelope failures when `success === false`.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/index.ts:883-887 :: the executor marks the tool call successful whenever `presentationEnvelope?.success !== false`.",
        "workflow: npx tsx <<'EOF' ... parseAgentBrowserEnvelope('{\"error\":\"boom\"}') ... EOF :: observed `parsed.envelope = { error: \"boom\" }`, `errorText = null`, and `presentation.summary = \"open completed\"`.",
        "workflow: npx tsx <<'EOF' ... fake agent-browser emits {\"error\":\"boom\"} ... EOF :: observed `result.isError = false`, `details.error = \"boom\"`, and `details.summary = \"open completed\"` for `open https://example.com`."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Require a boolean `success` field for non-batch JSON envelopes, or fail closed when a non-batch object carries an `error` without `success`.",
        "Update error derivation so malformed-but-JSON upstream payloads surface as protocol errors instead of empty successes.",
        "Add parser-level and fake-binary extension tests that cover missing-success envelopes.",
        "Verify by running `npm test` and confirming the missing-success fake-binary case returns `isError: true` with a non-empty error message."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: edge cases and bugs in the pi native agent_browser integration and agent-browser passthrough",
